1
00:00:01,126 --> 00:00:03,002
[Marcus] <i>That conference.</i>
<i>That's their target.</i>

2
00:00:03,086 --> 00:00:05,213
<i>That's where General Carillo will strike.</i>

3
00:00:05,296 --> 00:00:06,172
<i>General Villanueva.</i>

4
00:00:06,256 --> 00:00:08,133
<i>He's the only one</i>
<i>who could've recommended Domingo</i>

5
00:00:08,216 --> 00:00:10,010
<i>to join the President's security detail.</i>

6
00:00:10,093 --> 00:00:11,177
<i>He's working with General Carillo.</i>

7
00:00:11,261 --> 00:00:12,971
[Usman] <i>Jamilah,</i>
<i>Jalil's sister, and Dr. Reyes</i>

8
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:14,764
<i>was kidnapped by armed men.</i>

9
00:00:14,848 --> 00:00:17,100
[Axl] <i>I recognized one of the armed men.</i>

10
00:00:17,183 --> 00:00:19,519
He's one of Felix Domingo's men.

11
00:00:19,602 --> 00:00:20,270
‪[indistinct dialogue]

12
00:00:20,353 --> 00:00:21,855
[Maya Mae] <i>Alright. Go find the President.</i>

13
00:00:21,938 --> 00:00:23,106
[Jalil] <i>The President's not here.</i>

14
00:00:23,189 --> 00:00:24,524
[Marcus] <i>We need to find her.</i>

15
00:00:24,607 --> 00:00:26,359
[Sean] <i>Sir, they're attacking</i>
<i>Malacañang now.</i>

16
00:00:26,443 --> 00:00:27,527
[in English] Move! Move out!

17
00:00:29,320 --> 00:00:34,409
You have to declare Martial Law.

18
00:00:34,492 --> 00:00:35,326
[Natalia, in English]
<i>You will never succeed.</i>

19
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:37,537
<i>Don't underestimate the Filipinos.</i>

20
00:00:37,620 --> 00:00:41,416
Because they will never be fooled
by a psychopath like you!

21
00:00:41,499 --> 00:00:42,792
- [grunts]
- [Natalia yelps]

22
00:00:42,876 --> 00:00:44,669
[Villanueva] <i>Marcus Reyes</i>
<i>and Jalil Abubakar are here.</i>

23
00:00:44,753 --> 00:00:46,171
<i>They're inside.</i>

24
00:00:46,254 --> 00:00:47,088
[General Carillo] <i>And the news will say</i>

25
00:00:47,172 --> 00:00:51,426
<i>that you were killed</i>
<i>by Marcus Reyes and Jalil Abubakar</i>

26
00:00:51,509 --> 00:00:54,512
<i>to seize power.</i>

27
00:00:56,973 --> 00:00:58,516
[bomb activates, ticking]

28
00:01:04,272 --> 00:01:09,360
[mysterious theme music playing]

29
00:01:19,496 --> 00:01:22,082
- You know you don't stand a chance.
- [bomb ticking, beeping]

30
00:01:22,165 --> 00:01:23,958
The armed forces and the police

31
00:01:24,042 --> 00:01:26,294
will never trust you
or follow your orders.

32
00:01:26,377 --> 00:01:28,171
That's why you have no allies!

33
00:01:28,254 --> 00:01:29,756
That's where you're wrong!

34
00:01:30,507 --> 00:01:34,844
More than half
of the NLEA regional offices

35
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:38,097
and the armed forces
are already on our side!

36
00:01:38,181 --> 00:01:41,100
The 12th Infantry Battalion in Region VII

37
00:01:41,184 --> 00:01:42,769
is just waiting for the go signal.

38
00:01:42,852 --> 00:01:44,479
Impossible!

39
00:01:44,562 --> 00:01:46,564
You'll never get General Navarro!

40
00:01:46,648 --> 00:01:47,899
- [laughs wryly]
- [bomb ticking]

41
00:01:47,982 --> 00:01:50,110
We just spoke.

42
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:53,363
He's only waiting
for General Carillo's go signal.

43
00:01:53,446 --> 00:01:54,781
W-What about General Balagtas?

44
00:01:55,573 --> 00:01:58,952
His men are ready
to storm Malacañang for the coup.

45
00:01:59,035 --> 00:02:01,454
Solares! Madrigal! Let's go!

46
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:03,581
We have to leave! Move!

47
00:02:03,665 --> 00:02:04,999
[metal clacks]

48
00:02:05,083 --> 00:02:06,960
[tense music playing]

49
00:02:11,589 --> 00:02:13,049
You two…

50
00:02:14,134 --> 00:02:18,888
Stop interfering with my plans!

51
00:02:18,972 --> 00:02:20,390
Can't you see?

52
00:02:21,057 --> 00:02:23,476
This is what the Philippines needs!

53
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,686
What?

54
00:02:25,895 --> 00:02:28,273
Chaos? Violence?

55
00:02:28,773 --> 00:02:31,985
Injustice? Fear? Is that
what you want for every Filipino?

56
00:02:32,068 --> 00:02:35,488
Do you know why there's chaos?

57
00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:39,325
Why violence is everywhere?

58
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:44,539
[in English] It's because people
have too much freedom.

59
00:02:44,622 --> 00:02:49,502
They do whatever they want.

60
00:02:50,003 --> 00:02:51,504
[Manuel chuckles wryly] And…

61
00:02:51,588 --> 00:02:56,885
when one man's freedom
interferes with another man's freedom,

62
00:02:57,468 --> 00:02:58,970
conflict happens.

63
00:02:59,762 --> 00:03:00,930
Or worse…

64
00:03:01,806 --> 00:03:03,516
violence.

65
00:03:04,309 --> 00:03:05,184
Fear.

66
00:03:05,268 --> 00:03:08,771
And when people are afraid,

67
00:03:09,814 --> 00:03:13,401
they crave order.

68
00:03:14,611 --> 00:03:18,031
Order that can only come

69
00:03:18,114 --> 00:03:21,993
under an iron fist!

70
00:03:22,076 --> 00:03:23,119
No.

71
00:03:24,245 --> 00:03:28,166
We don't need an iron fist.
We need justice!

72
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:31,336
There's nothing you can do now.

73
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:35,924
In less than eight minutes,

74
00:03:36,007 --> 00:03:39,260
the republic will be mine.

75
00:03:39,344 --> 00:03:41,095
[tense music continues]

76
00:03:42,639 --> 00:03:45,266
[in English] Reyes…

77
00:03:46,684 --> 00:03:50,188
you can still redeem yourself, you know?

78
00:03:50,271 --> 00:03:55,610
You can be the SID's golden boy again.

79
00:03:56,152 --> 00:04:01,950
Don't throw away the name and reputation

80
00:04:02,033 --> 00:04:06,287
you've spent years building.

81
00:04:07,830 --> 00:04:13,962
All you have to do is join me

82
00:04:14,754 --> 00:04:19,968
and say that Jalil Abubakar
is the mastermind

83
00:04:20,051 --> 00:04:26,015
behind the government's destabilization.

84
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:32,105
No matter what you say, General Carillo,

85
00:04:33,314 --> 00:04:35,608
I'm not joining you.

86
00:04:36,818 --> 00:04:39,112
I won't betray Jalil.

87
00:04:42,407 --> 00:04:46,619
Why are you throwing away your name

88
00:04:46,703 --> 00:04:52,542
and reputation just to protect this man?

89
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:54,002
That's enough, Carillo!

90
00:04:54,961 --> 00:04:56,087
Enough!

91
00:04:57,755 --> 00:05:01,092
You'll never tear us apart!

92
00:05:01,175 --> 00:05:04,804
We already know the truth,
General Carillo.

93
00:05:06,222 --> 00:05:09,434
You're the one who bombed
the M/V Doña Emilia!

94
00:05:11,019 --> 00:05:12,895
You destroyed our entire family

95
00:05:14,188 --> 00:05:16,691
and tore Gabriel away from us!

96
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:20,987
Yes, I'm Gabriel.

97
00:05:23,114 --> 00:05:24,866
Marcus and I are brothers.

98
00:05:24,949 --> 00:05:26,200
And because of you,

99
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:30,580
because of your evil,
you destroyed our family!

100
00:05:31,789 --> 00:05:33,750
You can't tear us apart anymore.

101
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:38,713
And we won't let you do this
to another family

102
00:05:39,297 --> 00:05:40,798
because of your evil deeds!

103
00:05:40,882 --> 00:05:42,717
[dramatic sting]

104
00:05:47,847 --> 00:05:48,931
[in English] Move, move!

105
00:05:58,941 --> 00:06:00,735
There's a bomb planted on the President.

106
00:06:13,623 --> 00:06:15,041
[gunshots blasting]

107
00:06:17,001 --> 00:06:18,044
[in English] Down!

108
00:06:27,553 --> 00:06:29,597
[Azuelo] Drop your weapons! Now!

109
00:06:30,348 --> 00:06:33,017
[suspenseful music playing]

110
00:06:36,521 --> 00:06:38,147
- [Manuel grunts]
- General!

111
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:39,565
[Manuel groans]

112
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:42,026
Where do you think you're going,
General Manuel?

113
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:47,323
- [bomb ticking]
- [Natalia] Marcus, Jalil…

114
00:06:47,406 --> 00:06:48,366
[Jalil] Madam!

115
00:06:48,449 --> 00:06:50,284
[bomb ticking]

116
00:06:50,368 --> 00:06:51,786
- [grunts]
- Help me.

117
00:06:52,578 --> 00:06:53,704
[officer] This setup is way too advanced.

118
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:57,542
The collar and the strap
are connected to the bomb.

119
00:06:58,126 --> 00:06:59,085
We can't remove it.

120
00:07:00,628 --> 00:07:02,505
If we force it off, it'll explode.

121
00:07:04,507 --> 00:07:06,425
Flores, you can do this.

122
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:07,635
Defuse it.

123
00:07:08,594 --> 00:07:10,555
This is the first time
I've seen a setup like this.

124
00:07:10,638 --> 00:07:11,681
But…

125
00:07:11,764 --> 00:07:12,932
[panting]

126
00:07:13,015 --> 00:07:14,058
I'm taking my chances!

127
00:07:14,142 --> 00:07:17,478
- [tense music playing]
- [bomb ticking]

128
00:07:17,562 --> 00:07:20,773
- [Azuelo] <i>Move!</i>
- [Manuel laughing wryly]

129
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,110
[bomb ticking]

130
00:07:26,195 --> 00:07:28,114
[suspenseful music playing]

131
00:07:29,949 --> 00:07:31,701
- [bomb ticking]
- [breathes sharply]

132
00:07:31,784 --> 00:07:33,286
Hurry up! Hurry!

133
00:07:33,369 --> 00:07:35,955
[laughing wryly]

134
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:38,040
- [tense music playing]
- [bomb ticking]

135
00:07:47,884 --> 00:07:49,469
[laughs wryly]

136
00:07:50,052 --> 00:07:51,387
- [bomb ticking]
- [in English] Three…

137
00:07:52,346 --> 00:07:54,056
[in English] Two…

138
00:07:57,852 --> 00:07:58,811
- [in English] One!
- [bomb ticks]

139
00:08:00,438 --> 00:08:01,314
[in English] Boom!

140
00:08:04,358 --> 00:08:06,319
- [grunts]
- [whimpers]

141
00:08:06,402 --> 00:08:09,197
[Andre breathing heavily]

142
00:08:10,823 --> 00:08:12,241
[breathing heavily]

143
00:08:14,076 --> 00:08:16,496
[whimpering]

144
00:08:17,079 --> 00:08:18,039
[Natalia] Oh…

145
00:08:18,122 --> 00:08:20,082
[breathing sharply]

146
00:08:23,211 --> 00:08:28,382
[wailing, screaming]

147
00:08:28,466 --> 00:08:32,178
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

148
00:08:37,850 --> 00:08:40,978
[screaming]

149
00:08:41,062 --> 00:08:43,606
- [Manuel wailing]
- [Azuelo] Enough!

150
00:08:43,689 --> 00:08:46,150
Aah! Boom!

151
00:08:46,859 --> 00:08:47,902
Boom!

152
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:51,822
[Manuel groans]

153
00:08:51,906 --> 00:08:53,991
I already know who your accomplice is.

154
00:08:54,075 --> 00:08:55,076
[whimpers]

155
00:08:55,159 --> 00:08:56,619
You don't have anyone left on your side!

156
00:08:56,702 --> 00:08:59,455
They're all going to pay
for their crimes with you

157
00:08:59,539 --> 00:09:00,998
and rot in prison!

158
00:09:02,833 --> 00:09:04,919
Reyes, Jalil, I need to talk to you.

159
00:09:05,002 --> 00:09:08,756
You think you've won?

160
00:09:08,839 --> 00:09:11,259
- Huh?
- That's enough, Manuel!

161
00:09:11,842 --> 00:09:13,719
Don't celebrate just yet!

162
00:09:14,428 --> 00:09:19,559
Because I prepared a little insurance

163
00:09:19,642 --> 00:09:21,852
that I haven't used yet!

164
00:09:21,936 --> 00:09:26,440
I never expected you to make it out alive!

165
00:09:26,524 --> 00:09:28,109
What do you mean by that?

166
00:09:28,192 --> 00:09:29,402
- Talk!
- [Manuel laughing]

167
00:09:29,485 --> 00:09:32,113
- Say what you mean!
- [Manuel sighs]

168
00:09:32,196 --> 00:09:37,326
Do you even know…

169
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:38,452
[panting]

170
00:09:38,536 --> 00:09:43,249
…where your loved ones are?

171
00:09:43,332 --> 00:09:44,458
- [Jalil] Where are they?
- [Manuel laughs wryly]

172
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:45,876
- [Jalil] Where are they?
- [Azuelo] Jalil!

173
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:46,877
- [laughing]
- Where are they?

174
00:09:46,961 --> 00:09:48,004
- [laughing]
- Jalil!

175
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:53,134
Reyes, Felix kidnapped your mother.
And Jamilah too.

176
00:09:54,010 --> 00:09:55,011
- What?
- What?

177
00:09:55,094 --> 00:09:56,554
[phone ringing]

178
00:09:58,681 --> 00:10:00,683
- Felix!
- [Felix] <i>Marcus!</i>

179
00:10:00,766 --> 00:10:05,104
Jalil! I have a surprise for all of you!

180
00:10:05,187 --> 00:10:07,023
‪[suspenseful music playing]

181
00:10:07,106 --> 00:10:08,733
- [Jamilah] Jalil!
- [Teresa] Marcus!

182
00:10:08,816 --> 00:10:10,651
- Ma!
- Marcus…

183
00:10:10,735 --> 00:10:12,153
- [Felix] Watch them!
- Gabriel…

184
00:10:12,236 --> 00:10:13,988
- [Teresa] My sons…
- Jalil!

185
00:10:14,071 --> 00:10:15,823
- Felix, you bastard!
- Felix!

186
00:10:17,325 --> 00:10:20,453
Felix, where are you?
Where did you take our family?

187
00:10:20,536 --> 00:10:21,537
[Felix] We're here…

188
00:10:22,955 --> 00:10:26,083
at the West Tower of the Tayum Building!

189
00:10:26,667 --> 00:10:27,627
[Felix] <i>So…</i>

190
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:30,630
Get over here now.

191
00:10:30,713 --> 00:10:33,299
[tense music playing]

192
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:42,433
- [Manuel screaming]
- Marcus, Jalil,

193
00:10:42,516 --> 00:10:44,769
save your family! Hurry up!

194
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:46,228
- [Azuelo] Move! Move! Go! Go!
- Let's go.

195
00:10:46,312 --> 00:10:48,648
- [laughing]
- [in English] Goddammit! Shut up!

196
00:10:48,731 --> 00:10:49,732
Get him in the van!

197
00:10:49,815 --> 00:10:51,275
[Manuel groans]

198
00:10:51,359 --> 00:10:54,945
- Felix, why are you doing this?
- [Jamilah sobs]

199
00:10:55,696 --> 00:10:59,283
If you and Marcus have a problem,
you can talk it out, can't you?

200
00:11:00,743 --> 00:11:03,287
You've worked together for so long.

201
00:11:03,371 --> 00:11:04,705
Shut up.

202
00:11:05,456 --> 00:11:07,291
You don't know what you're talking about.

203
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:11,212
Your son has wronged me.

204
00:11:13,339 --> 00:11:14,465
Your brother!

205
00:11:15,424 --> 00:11:18,386
No matter how much
we talk it out… [sharp inhale]

206
00:11:19,345 --> 00:11:20,721
we can't fix it anymore.

207
00:11:21,639 --> 00:11:23,766
They took so much from me.

208
00:11:23,849 --> 00:11:25,601
Have you gone mad?

209
00:11:27,186 --> 00:11:31,190
No matter what you do,
you won't be able to beat them

210
00:11:31,273 --> 00:11:35,319
because they're better than you!

211
00:11:35,403 --> 00:11:36,987
- [Jamilah groans]
- [Teresa] Jamilah!

212
00:11:37,071 --> 00:11:40,032
They can't do anything to me!

213
00:11:40,116 --> 00:11:41,325
[whimpers]

214
00:11:42,118 --> 00:11:44,912
Because I have the edge. I have the edge!

215
00:11:45,496 --> 00:11:46,956
I have both of you, don't I?

216
00:11:47,832 --> 00:11:49,917
[suspenseful music playing]

217
00:11:55,172 --> 00:12:00,177
- I will make them suffer… slowly.
- [Teresa sobbing]

218
00:12:02,138 --> 00:12:04,223
- [Jamilah sobs]
- With pain that will cut through…

219
00:12:06,475 --> 00:12:07,560
their soul.

220
00:12:08,269 --> 00:12:10,438
[suspenseful music continues]

221
00:12:19,989 --> 00:12:22,283
Where could Domingo have taken them?

222
00:12:22,366 --> 00:12:24,034
[Jalil] Jamilah!

223
00:12:24,118 --> 00:12:25,077
- [Marcus] Ma!
- Jalil!

224
00:12:25,161 --> 00:12:26,537
- [Jalil] Jamilah!
- No! Stop!

225
00:12:26,620 --> 00:12:28,080
- [Jamilah] Stop!
- This is a trap!

226
00:12:28,914 --> 00:12:30,499
[masked man, in English]
Let's move! Men, let's move!

227
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:33,419
- [grunting, groaning]
- Stop!

228
00:12:33,502 --> 00:12:35,546
- [man grunts]
- [Jamilah] Stop that!

229
00:12:36,547 --> 00:12:37,965
[suspenseful music continues]

230
00:12:38,048 --> 00:12:39,842
- [Jamilah] Jalil!
- [Teresa] Stop!

231
00:12:40,593 --> 00:12:41,427
[phone buzzing]

232
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:42,887
Ethan, any update?

233
00:12:42,970 --> 00:12:45,389
Sir Usman, Buster and I
managed to trace the van!

234
00:12:45,473 --> 00:12:47,016
I'll send you the location right now.

235
00:12:48,684 --> 00:12:49,768
[electronic whirring]

236
00:12:49,852 --> 00:12:50,686
[device beeps]

237
00:12:50,769 --> 00:12:52,271
- Here it is!
- Give me that.

238
00:12:53,522 --> 00:12:56,609
[suspenseful music continues]

239
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:06,660
You're all so shameless!

240
00:13:09,121 --> 00:13:10,623
[in English] Goddammit!

241
00:13:13,834 --> 00:13:14,960
Take them in.

242
00:13:17,338 --> 00:13:19,381
[cops booing]

243
00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:21,133
[man 1] You're finally arrested!

244
00:13:21,217 --> 00:13:22,384
[man 2] How shameless!

245
00:13:22,468 --> 00:13:24,136
[man 1] Our agency
will finally be in order!

246
00:13:24,220 --> 00:13:26,347
[man 3] That's what you deserve!

247
00:13:26,430 --> 00:13:27,806
[man 2] You're going to rot in jail!

248
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:30,100
[suspenseful music continues]

249
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:34,813
- [Teresa and Jamilah crying]
- [Jalil panting]

250
00:13:37,024 --> 00:13:38,442
- [Felix] Wow!
- You're an animal.

251
00:13:38,526 --> 00:13:40,611
- Yes, I am.
- You bastard!

252
00:13:40,694 --> 00:13:43,531
- [Marcus] Felix!
- We're going to play a game!

253
00:13:44,782 --> 00:13:46,784
- [Felix grunting]
- [Marcus] Stop this, Felix!

254
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:49,119
- Felix, don't!
- Felix, stop this!

255
00:13:49,203 --> 00:13:50,454
[Jalil] Face me instead!

256
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:51,914
- That's enough!
- You bastard!

257
00:13:51,997 --> 00:13:52,873
- [Jamilah screams]
- [Teresa grunts]

258
00:13:52,957 --> 00:13:54,875
[Marcus] Bring them down, you bastard!

259
00:13:54,959 --> 00:13:57,419
- Bring them down!
- Felix! Stop it!

260
00:13:58,379 --> 00:13:59,213
Fine!

261
00:13:59,296 --> 00:14:02,800
Felix, Carillo has been arrested already!

262
00:14:02,883 --> 00:14:05,302
So, what you're fighting for
is already meaningless. Felix--

263
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:08,180
[dramatic stinging]

264
00:14:09,515 --> 00:14:12,101
- Shall we play a game?
- [breathing heavily]

265
00:14:12,184 --> 00:14:14,061
Who do you want me to shoot first?

266
00:14:14,144 --> 00:14:15,312
[Teresa gasps]

267
00:14:16,897 --> 00:14:21,026
- [Jalil] Felix! Felix, you bastard!
- That's enough, Felix!

268
00:14:21,110 --> 00:14:22,570
- Her?
- [Teresa] Felix, no!

269
00:14:22,653 --> 00:14:23,571
Mom!

270
00:14:23,654 --> 00:14:26,198
- [Jamilah crying]
- Or your brother?

271
00:14:26,282 --> 00:14:28,158
Felix, stop this already!

272
00:14:28,242 --> 00:14:30,619
Just shoot me instead, Felix!

273
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:33,789
- Just don't shoot Jamilah!
- [Jamilah] Doctor, no!

274
00:14:33,873 --> 00:14:36,250
Have mercy on her! Just shoot me instead!

275
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:37,710
Wow!

276
00:14:38,711 --> 00:14:40,921
We have so many heroes here.

277
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:42,882
[dramatic stinging]

278
00:14:42,965 --> 00:14:45,676
- [blank fire]
- [Marcus] Felix! Ma!

279
00:14:45,759 --> 00:14:47,261
[Jamilah] No!

280
00:14:47,344 --> 00:14:49,763
- [Marcus grunts]
- Oh, it's a blank!

281
00:14:50,306 --> 00:14:52,474
- [Teresa whimpering]
- [Felix] Who will get shot next?

282
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:54,810
- [Jalil] Felix, no!
- [Marcus] Not Jamilah!

283
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:56,395
- [Jalil] Felix! No, Felix!
- [Marcus] Jamilah.

284
00:14:56,478 --> 00:14:58,606
Felix, don't do that! Stop this already!

285
00:14:58,689 --> 00:15:02,735
[tense music continues]

286
00:15:09,199 --> 00:15:11,660
- [blank fire]
- [Jalil] Felix! Jamilah!

287
00:15:11,744 --> 00:15:15,039
Oh? Oops. It's still a blank.

288
00:15:16,290 --> 00:15:19,418
- You will pay for this!
- [Felix] How will you fight back?

289
00:15:20,294 --> 00:15:23,505
I'm in control of this situation!

290
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:24,882
[tense music continues]

291
00:15:24,965 --> 00:15:25,966
[Felix] Her?

292
00:15:26,050 --> 00:15:27,843
- [Jamilah sobs]
- [Jalil] Felix.

293
00:15:27,927 --> 00:15:29,011
- [blank fire]
- Bang!

294
00:15:29,094 --> 00:15:31,972
- [Teresa screams]
- You bastard! You're an animal!

295
00:15:32,056 --> 00:15:33,849
- Or her?
- [Jamilah screams]

296
00:15:33,933 --> 00:15:35,935
- [Jalil] Jamilah!
- Bang!

297
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:37,519
[Felix] Oh, wow!

298
00:15:37,603 --> 00:15:40,439
- [Teresa sobbing]
- You're so lucky!

299
00:15:40,522 --> 00:15:42,691
‪[dramatic stinging]

300
00:15:42,775 --> 00:15:45,152
[tense music continues]

301
00:15:47,404 --> 00:15:50,366
- [Felix] So what will we do now?
- [Jamilah whimpering]

302
00:15:50,449 --> 00:15:52,493
What do you think my next shot will be?

303
00:15:52,576 --> 00:15:53,827
- You're an animal, Felix.
- [Felix] Really?

304
00:15:53,911 --> 00:15:55,412
- And what about you?
- Stop!

305
00:15:55,496 --> 00:15:57,581
- [Jalil] Felix!
- [Teresa] Stop, please!

306
00:15:57,665 --> 00:16:00,209
You've been in harm's way
many times, but here you are.

307
00:16:00,292 --> 00:16:02,461
You're still alive.
What a very lucky person.

308
00:16:02,544 --> 00:16:04,588
But now, let's see.

309
00:16:04,672 --> 00:16:07,132
Let's see if your luck
can save you from this!

310
00:16:07,216 --> 00:16:09,009
I've shot four times already.

311
00:16:09,093 --> 00:16:10,427
There are only two left.

312
00:16:11,679 --> 00:16:13,555
- [blank fire]
- [Jalil] Felix! Felix!

313
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:15,307
[Teresa whimpering]

314
00:16:15,391 --> 00:16:16,934
Felix!

315
00:16:17,017 --> 00:16:19,269
[tense music continues]

316
00:16:21,981 --> 00:16:23,273
- [grunts]
- [snaps]

317
00:16:24,733 --> 00:16:26,026
[groans]

318
00:16:26,110 --> 00:16:28,195
- [Jamilah sobs] Jalil…
- Listen to me.

319
00:16:28,278 --> 00:16:29,279
Haven't you been looking for me
for a long time

320
00:16:29,363 --> 00:16:30,614
because of what I've done to you?

321
00:16:31,949 --> 00:16:34,743
[Jalil] I'm the one
who gave you that scar.

322
00:16:34,827 --> 00:16:36,537
That was me!

323
00:16:37,329 --> 00:16:38,914
[man grunting]

324
00:16:40,666 --> 00:16:42,334
[grunting and groaning]

325
00:16:42,418 --> 00:16:43,711
Point that gun at me!

326
00:16:43,794 --> 00:16:44,962
- [Jamilah] Jalil, no!
- Felix, don't!

327
00:16:45,045 --> 00:16:47,506
- Gabriel, don't! Felix, don't!
- Jalil!

328
00:16:47,589 --> 00:16:49,425
- Do it!
- [Jamilah] Don't!

329
00:16:49,508 --> 00:16:51,510
- Do it.
- [Marcus] Don't!

330
00:16:51,593 --> 00:16:52,720
[Jalil] I'm the one
who gave you that scar.

331
00:16:52,803 --> 00:16:55,889
Don't, Felix! Not my brother, you bastard!

332
00:16:55,973 --> 00:16:57,766
- [Marcus] Not him!
- I'm right here.

333
00:16:57,850 --> 00:16:59,184
[exhales]

334
00:16:59,268 --> 00:17:00,811
- I'm here.
- Huh?

335
00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:04,023
So this is your brother, Gabriel?

336
00:17:04,106 --> 00:17:05,649
[tense music playing]

337
00:17:08,402 --> 00:17:10,154
Jalil Abubakar?

338
00:17:10,237 --> 00:17:12,364
[Jamilah sobbing]

339
00:17:12,906 --> 00:17:14,366
Now, Marcus…

340
00:17:15,409 --> 00:17:16,744
I know…

341
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:19,580
exactly how to hurt you.

342
00:17:21,123 --> 00:17:22,875
You bastard! Let go of my mother!

343
00:17:22,958 --> 00:17:25,085
- [Teresa breathing heavily]
- Why?

344
00:17:25,711 --> 00:17:26,879
You're trying to be a hero?

345
00:17:26,962 --> 00:17:28,380
- [Jamilah screams]
- [Teresa] Don't!

346
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:29,757
Marcus!

347
00:17:29,840 --> 00:17:32,760
[dramatic stinging]

348
00:17:33,969 --> 00:17:35,387
Felix!

349
00:17:38,015 --> 00:17:39,516
[Jamilah sobbing]

350
00:17:40,684 --> 00:17:41,643
- [Jamilah screaming]
- [Teresa] No!

351
00:17:41,727 --> 00:17:43,187
[gun clatters]

352
00:17:44,188 --> 00:17:46,190
[grunting and groaning]

353
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,234
[grunts]

354
00:17:49,318 --> 00:17:50,611
[gunshots blasting]

355
00:17:50,694 --> 00:17:52,654
- [Marcus] Hurry! Untie me!
- [Usman] Brother.

356
00:17:54,239 --> 00:17:55,282
Felix!

357
00:17:55,365 --> 00:17:56,784
[Marcus grunts]

358
00:17:56,867 --> 00:17:58,035
Sir Marcus!

359
00:17:59,203 --> 00:18:01,580
- [man grunts]
- [gunshots blasting]

360
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:04,750
- Felix!
- [gunshots blasting]

361
00:18:10,672 --> 00:18:12,674
[suspenseful music playing]

362
00:18:12,758 --> 00:18:14,468
[rapid gunfire]

363
00:18:21,600 --> 00:18:23,685
- [gunshot]
- Domingo!

364
00:18:25,020 --> 00:18:26,730
You bastard!

365
00:18:27,773 --> 00:18:29,942
You killed my brothers!

366
00:18:31,068 --> 00:18:33,779
Jovi! Tommy!

367
00:18:34,488 --> 00:18:35,823
You promised…

368
00:18:37,116 --> 00:18:39,159
- you'd take care of us!
- Shh.

369
00:18:39,243 --> 00:18:40,452
You killed them!

370
00:18:40,536 --> 00:18:41,703
Yeah! Calm down!

371
00:18:41,787 --> 00:18:43,997
[grunting]

372
00:18:44,081 --> 00:18:45,082
- [Axl grunts]
- [gunshot]

373
00:18:45,165 --> 00:18:46,333
Domingo!

374
00:18:46,834 --> 00:18:48,669
[gunshots blasting]

375
00:18:51,171 --> 00:18:52,256
[Usman grunts]

376
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,049
- Idiot!
- [gunshots]

377
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:57,803
- Usman!
- [gunshots]

378
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:04,768
- Usman! Usman!
- Go ahead, brother!

379
00:19:04,852 --> 00:19:06,270
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

380
00:19:06,353 --> 00:19:07,938
I'll be fine. Go after Domingo!

381
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:10,190
- [Marcus grunts]
- [gunshots]

382
00:19:15,112 --> 00:19:17,948
[suspenseful music continues]

383
00:19:29,001 --> 00:19:30,043
[gun clicks]

384
00:19:30,127 --> 00:19:32,754
[suspenseful music continues]

385
00:19:37,718 --> 00:19:39,052
[Felix grunting]

386
00:19:39,136 --> 00:19:40,637
[grunting, groaning]

387
00:19:44,766 --> 00:19:46,018
- [gunshot]
- [grunting]

388
00:19:46,101 --> 00:19:47,644
- [both grunting]
- [gunshot]

389
00:19:48,979 --> 00:19:50,022
- [Gunshot]
- [Jalil grunts]

390
00:19:52,107 --> 00:19:53,483
- [gunshots]
- [Marcus grunts]

391
00:19:53,567 --> 00:19:56,320
[suspenseful music continues]

392
00:19:57,070 --> 00:19:59,072
[screaming]

393
00:19:59,156 --> 00:20:00,490
Gabriel!

394
00:20:02,451 --> 00:20:03,452
[thuds]

395
00:20:03,535 --> 00:20:06,330
[suspenseful music continues]

396
00:20:06,413 --> 00:20:07,623
[Marcus grunts]

397
00:20:09,958 --> 00:20:12,002
[Jalil grunts]

398
00:20:12,502 --> 00:20:14,630
[suspenseful music continues]

399
00:20:14,713 --> 00:20:16,757
[Marcus] Gabriel, hold on!

400
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:17,966
[Jalil grunts]

401
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:19,343
Don't let go!

402
00:20:20,344 --> 00:20:21,470
[grunting]

403
00:20:23,388 --> 00:20:26,683
[young Marcus] <i>Gabriel, hold on!</i>
<i>Don't let go!</i>

404
00:20:26,767 --> 00:20:28,810
[young Gabriel] <i>Marcus,</i>
<i>I can't hold on anymore!</i>

405
00:20:28,894 --> 00:20:30,187
No!

406
00:20:31,855 --> 00:20:32,940
- [Gabriel grunts]
- No!

407
00:20:33,690 --> 00:20:35,609
[suspenseful music continues]

408
00:20:37,611 --> 00:20:39,321
- Gabriel!
- Marcus, let me go!

409
00:20:39,404 --> 00:20:40,822
- No!
- I can't hold on anymore!

410
00:20:41,657 --> 00:20:43,408
- I already lost you once…
- [grunts]

411
00:20:44,284 --> 00:20:48,080
We didn't come this far…
just to lose you again!

412
00:20:48,747 --> 00:20:49,581
[grunts]

413
00:20:49,665 --> 00:20:51,124
- Hold on!
- [Gabriel grunts]

414
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:53,627
[suspenseful music continues]

415
00:20:54,419 --> 00:20:55,545
Let me go!

416
00:20:56,713 --> 00:20:57,881
No!

417
00:21:02,803 --> 00:21:04,638
[Marcus grunts]

418
00:21:08,308 --> 00:21:09,559
[both grunting]

419
00:21:12,396 --> 00:21:15,065
[both breathing heavily]

420
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:20,570
[gasps]

421
00:21:21,989 --> 00:21:26,451
Marcus… Marcus, thank you. Thank you…

422
00:21:27,452 --> 00:21:30,706
- [Marcus breathing heavily]
- [chuckling]

423
00:21:39,214 --> 00:21:41,049
- [dog whimpers]
- [melodramatic music playing]

424
00:21:45,595 --> 00:21:46,638
[gasps]

425
00:21:47,514 --> 00:21:50,559
Cuchy… Thank you so much.

426
00:21:53,061 --> 00:21:54,855
You were the only one…

427
00:21:57,274 --> 00:21:59,192
who ever loved me.

428
00:21:59,276 --> 00:22:01,987
[dog whimpers]

429
00:22:09,995 --> 00:22:11,246
Cuchy!

430
00:22:13,874 --> 00:22:14,916
Cuchy!

431
00:22:33,268 --> 00:22:34,519
[grunts]

432
00:22:34,603 --> 00:22:36,021
Watch your step.

433
00:22:37,689 --> 00:22:39,399
[grunting]

434
00:22:46,907 --> 00:22:50,619
- My sons! Marcus! Gabriel!
- [Marcus] Mama…

435
00:22:52,287 --> 00:22:53,622
[Marcus, in English] Attendance check.

436
00:22:55,582 --> 00:22:56,875
Your sons are safe.

437
00:22:59,086 --> 00:23:00,420
[Marcus] Don't worry.

438
00:23:02,422 --> 00:23:03,590
You two…

439
00:23:04,299 --> 00:23:06,635
Just because your mother is a doctor

440
00:23:06,718 --> 00:23:08,970
and, Jalil, your sister is a nurse,

441
00:23:09,054 --> 00:23:12,349
doesn't mean you should keep
throwing yourselves into danger.

442
00:23:13,475 --> 00:23:14,684
- Let's go.
- Come on.

443
00:23:14,768 --> 00:23:16,645
Let's go to the hospital.

444
00:23:17,395 --> 00:23:19,189
- Come on, sons.
- [Jamilah] Let's go.

445
00:23:19,272 --> 00:23:21,316
[dramatic music swells]

446
00:23:21,399 --> 00:23:24,444
[reporter] According to the authorities,
the attack on Malacanang

447
00:23:24,528 --> 00:23:29,074
was allegedly part of a plan
to destabilize the country.

448
00:23:29,157 --> 00:23:33,787
<i>And the mastermind behind it</i>
<i>is retired Police General Manuel Carillo.</i>

449
00:23:33,870 --> 00:23:36,123
<i>He is also believed to be</i>
<i>the leader of the syndicate</i>

450
00:23:36,206 --> 00:23:38,500
<i>responsible for trafficking</i>
<i>illegal firearms</i>

451
00:23:38,583 --> 00:23:40,710
<i>and orchestrating the series</i>
<i>of violent incidents recently.</i>

452
00:23:41,211 --> 00:23:44,256
<i>President Natalia Mendoza</i>
<i>survived the attack</i>

453
00:23:44,339 --> 00:23:47,968
<i>thanks to Agent Marcus Reyes</i>
<i>and Jalil Abubakar.</i>

454
00:23:48,051 --> 00:23:51,388
The two were recently placed under

455
00:23:51,471 --> 00:23:53,223
a "neutralize on sight" order,

456
00:23:53,306 --> 00:23:57,185
but their names have now
been fully cleared.

457
00:23:57,269 --> 00:24:01,106
Carillo and his accomplices
are currently detained

458
00:24:01,189 --> 00:24:03,608
as they stand trial for their cases.

459
00:24:03,692 --> 00:24:06,653
[in English] Okay.
Let's give credit where credit is due.

460
00:24:06,736 --> 00:24:09,948
Agent Marcus Reyes and Jalil Abubakar,

461
00:24:10,490 --> 00:24:13,743
thank you very much
for the heroism you've shown.

462
00:24:13,827 --> 00:24:18,582
You risked your lives
not only for Madam President,

463
00:24:18,665 --> 00:24:22,043
but also for the future
of the Filipino people.

464
00:24:22,127 --> 00:24:24,296
I pray to Allah

465
00:24:24,921 --> 00:24:27,757
that he will guide and protect you
in every mission

466
00:24:27,841 --> 00:24:30,468
and every decision you make.

467
00:24:30,552 --> 00:24:35,140
And I hope this serves
as a warning to all of us.

468
00:24:35,223 --> 00:24:37,225
We have the right to investigate.

469
00:24:37,309 --> 00:24:40,812
Let's recognize who truly
serves the people

470
00:24:40,896 --> 00:24:44,691
and hold accountable
those who betray the public's trust.

471
00:24:44,774 --> 00:24:45,775
- [in English] Correct.
- Right?

472
00:24:45,859 --> 00:24:51,114
Like what Agent Marcus Reyes
and Jalil Abubakar did.

473
00:24:51,198 --> 00:24:52,490
[in English] True!

474
00:24:53,742 --> 00:24:55,994
[melodramatic music playing]

475
00:25:33,615 --> 00:25:35,784
[applause]

476
00:25:42,457 --> 00:25:46,461
[in English] Our republic recently faced
a serious threat

477
00:25:47,087 --> 00:25:50,674
from individuals who sought to seize power

478
00:25:51,508 --> 00:25:53,843
and throw our nation into chaos.

479
00:25:54,552 --> 00:25:59,766
But through the bravery, courage,

480
00:25:59,849 --> 00:26:03,186
and sacrifice of our brave men and women

481
00:26:03,270 --> 00:26:07,399
who risked their lives
to defend our nation,

482
00:26:09,067 --> 00:26:11,236
that threat has been defeated.

483
00:26:13,196 --> 00:26:16,157
Now I want every Filipino to know this.

484
00:26:17,409 --> 00:26:20,412
The Republic is safe once again.

485
00:26:20,495 --> 00:26:23,290
And our democracy remains strong,

486
00:26:23,373 --> 00:26:26,209
our institutions stand firm,

487
00:26:26,293 --> 00:26:30,171
and our nation will move forward, united.

488
00:26:30,255 --> 00:26:32,132
[applause]

489
00:26:38,888 --> 00:26:40,432
[camera shutters clicking]

490
00:26:45,478 --> 00:26:48,106
I just want to thank you again,
Agent Marcus Reyes,

491
00:26:48,189 --> 00:26:50,108
and the rest of your colleagues.

492
00:26:50,191 --> 00:26:53,695
You didn't just save my life,
but also the entire Philippines.

493
00:26:53,778 --> 00:26:55,697
Thank you, Madam President.

494
00:26:56,489 --> 00:26:57,657
It is my duty.

495
00:26:58,366 --> 00:27:00,577
And to you as well, Jalil Abubakar.

496
00:27:00,660 --> 00:27:02,871
I will never forget your bravery.

497
00:27:03,955 --> 00:27:07,125
Police officers, soldiers,

498
00:27:07,792 --> 00:27:09,085
or even civilians like me…

499
00:27:09,794 --> 00:27:14,257
We all have a responsibility
to protect our country.

500
00:27:15,133 --> 00:27:18,678
I also want to offer my condolences
for the loss of your father.

501
00:27:19,262 --> 00:27:22,932
I know how painful it is
to lose your loved ones.

502
00:27:23,892 --> 00:27:27,187
Even now, I'm still grieving…

503
00:27:27,270 --> 00:27:29,272
the loss of my close friend, Ahmad.

504
00:27:29,981 --> 00:27:33,610
Thank you, madam,
and… I'm sorry for your loss.

505
00:27:35,403 --> 00:27:38,031
I would like to think that…

506
00:27:38,823 --> 00:27:41,409
their sacrifices weren't in vain.

507
00:27:42,827 --> 00:27:47,916
Ah, Jalil, if you want
to stay in the police force,

508
00:27:48,583 --> 00:27:49,501
just let me know.

509
00:27:50,210 --> 00:27:52,462
[melodramatic music playing]

510
00:27:54,547 --> 00:27:57,384
Thank you, madam. Thank you.

511
00:28:13,108 --> 00:28:15,735
Take care on your trip
back to the island, okay?

512
00:28:17,445 --> 00:28:20,573
Is Sitti already in the car?

513
00:28:20,657 --> 00:28:23,284
She didn't want to come back out
because she might just start crying again.

514
00:28:23,368 --> 00:28:24,619
[both chuckle]

515
00:28:24,702 --> 00:28:25,870
Auntie…

516
00:28:27,914 --> 00:28:29,082
Thank you.

517
00:28:29,165 --> 00:28:32,419
[gentle music playing]

518
00:28:32,502 --> 00:28:34,045
Thank you.

519
00:28:37,340 --> 00:28:40,552
Uncle, even though…
we're not blood-related,

520
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:43,221
you accepted us.

521
00:28:43,972 --> 00:28:45,181
You loved us.

522
00:28:45,974 --> 00:28:47,183
You embraced us.

523
00:28:48,059 --> 00:28:49,144
Don't mention it.

524
00:28:49,811 --> 00:28:52,063
We don't need to be related by blood

525
00:28:52,147 --> 00:28:54,232
for us to treat you like family.

526
00:28:54,315 --> 00:28:55,650
You are family.

527
00:28:56,151 --> 00:28:57,235
Take care, okay?

528
00:28:59,237 --> 00:29:01,906
- [Jamilah] Thank you.
- [Norhana] I'll miss you.

529
00:29:01,990 --> 00:29:04,868
- Take care.
- [Jamilah] Take care.

530
00:29:04,951 --> 00:29:07,245
- [in Tausug] Thank you.
- [Omar] Take care.

531
00:29:08,455 --> 00:29:09,706
- Auntie.
- Jalil.

532
00:29:10,331 --> 00:29:11,875
[Norhana chuckles softly]

533
00:29:13,626 --> 00:29:16,379
Shh, shh.

534
00:29:21,509 --> 00:29:25,346
Mister Omar, Miss Norhana, thank you.

535
00:29:25,930 --> 00:29:27,390
Thank you so much.

536
00:29:28,183 --> 00:29:30,018
Don't mention it, Doc Teresa.

537
00:29:34,355 --> 00:29:35,607
Sir Marcus.

538
00:29:36,983 --> 00:29:38,526
Take care of them, okay?

539
00:29:39,110 --> 00:29:42,822
Make sure they arrive safely
at the airport.

540
00:29:42,906 --> 00:29:43,907
Promise me.

541
00:29:44,491 --> 00:29:46,659
- I promise.
- Thank you.

542
00:29:49,537 --> 00:29:51,372
- Thank you, Uncle.
- Be careful.

543
00:29:53,833 --> 00:29:55,126
[Teresa] Thank you.

544
00:29:55,210 --> 00:29:56,878
- Thank you.
- Jamilah.

545
00:29:58,880 --> 00:30:02,050
[sentimental music playing]

546
00:30:06,971 --> 00:30:09,224
After everything we've been through

547
00:30:09,808 --> 00:30:11,851
and everything that happened,

548
00:30:12,477 --> 00:30:14,270
there's one thing I've realized.

549
00:30:16,606 --> 00:30:18,066
[in English] I admire you.

550
00:30:20,401 --> 00:30:21,528
I like you.

551
00:30:27,700 --> 00:30:28,576
[Jalil] Marcus.

552
00:30:31,412 --> 00:30:32,622
Gabriel…

553
00:30:33,706 --> 00:30:35,834
I respect your family.

554
00:30:36,751 --> 00:30:39,212
I respect your beliefs.

555
00:30:52,642 --> 00:30:55,937
[music intensifies]

556
00:30:56,020 --> 00:30:57,105
- Take care.
- Take care.

557
00:30:57,772 --> 00:30:58,857
- Take care.
- Bye.

558
00:30:58,940 --> 00:31:00,358
Take care, Sir Marcus.

559
00:31:00,441 --> 00:31:01,818
- Take care.
- Take care.

560
00:31:12,954 --> 00:31:14,581
[melancholic music Playing]

561
00:31:14,664 --> 00:31:17,417
I brought Father back
to our island too late.

562
00:31:18,167 --> 00:31:20,211
I hope he can forgive me.

563
00:31:22,005 --> 00:31:23,423
[Jamilah] Jalil.

564
00:31:24,257 --> 00:31:27,218
I'm sure father is happy and at peace,

565
00:31:27,969 --> 00:31:30,597
knowing you've fulfilled
his wish to be brought home.

566
00:31:30,680 --> 00:31:35,143
[melancholic music playing]

567
00:31:41,608 --> 00:31:43,693
Gabriel just got back to the island,

568
00:31:43,776 --> 00:31:45,862
but you’ve already finished
fixing up his room.

569
00:31:45,945 --> 00:31:49,282
Of course, Ma. That way,
whenever he feels like visiting,

570
00:31:49,365 --> 00:31:50,199
this place is ready.

571
00:31:50,783 --> 00:31:52,243
I want him to know
that no matter what happens,

572
00:31:52,327 --> 00:31:53,536
he has a home to come back to here.

573
00:32:15,975 --> 00:32:20,104
[Maya Mae] <i>Everything started</i>
<i>on a tiny island in Mindanao.</i>

574
00:32:20,188 --> 00:32:21,481
<i>Damai Island.</i>

575
00:32:22,315 --> 00:32:26,402
A quiet and quaint community
barely noticeable on the map.

576
00:32:26,945 --> 00:32:28,988
But who would have thought

577
00:32:29,072 --> 00:32:32,158
that the battle which began
on a small island

578
00:32:32,825 --> 00:32:34,744
- [rapid gunfire]
- would reach the very center

579
00:32:34,827 --> 00:32:36,245
of our country's power?

580
00:32:36,329 --> 00:32:38,206
- [rapid gunfire]
- [morose music playing]

581
00:32:40,208 --> 00:32:42,001
[Natalia] <i>These past few days,</i>

582
00:32:42,085 --> 00:32:44,253
<i>our country has been put to the test.</i>

583
00:32:45,380 --> 00:32:48,132
<i>Our institutions have been tested.</i>

584
00:32:48,216 --> 00:32:51,928
Our trust in one another has been tested.

585
00:32:52,512 --> 00:32:53,930
Many have been hurt.

586
00:32:54,597 --> 00:32:56,933
<i>Many have sacrificed their lives.</i>

587
00:32:57,016 --> 00:32:59,060
<i>And many have questioned</i>

588
00:32:59,769 --> 00:33:02,230
<i>whether there is still hope</i>
<i>for our country.</i>

589
00:33:02,313 --> 00:33:04,857
<i>We have passed these tests.</i>

590
00:33:06,275 --> 00:33:09,737
But we must remain vigilant.

591
00:33:09,821 --> 00:33:13,491
Because there will always
be forces that will attempt

592
00:33:14,033 --> 00:33:16,244
to cause trouble
and take power for themselves.

593
00:33:17,537 --> 00:33:20,206
[Marcus] <i>It does not start with bullets.</i>

594
00:33:21,332 --> 00:33:25,336
<i>They begin with the stories</i>
<i>they want us to believe.</i>

595
00:33:25,420 --> 00:33:26,796
[Jalil] <i>With fear.</i>

596
00:33:26,879 --> 00:33:28,256
<i>Anger.</i>

597
00:33:29,048 --> 00:33:32,468
<i>In the stories they repeat</i>
<i>until they seem like the truth.</i>

598
00:33:33,428 --> 00:33:34,971
[Marcus] <i>The true battle</i>

599
00:33:35,555 --> 00:33:38,224
<i>is not just that of our soldiers,</i>

600
00:33:38,808 --> 00:33:41,394
<i>police, or public officials.</i>

601
00:33:41,477 --> 00:33:44,272
[Jalil] <i>It's also the fight</i>
<i>of every citizen who's willing</i>

602
00:33:44,355 --> 00:33:46,149
<i>to ask questions, to listen,</i>

603
00:33:46,816 --> 00:33:49,485
<i>and to find the truth before</i>
<i>they choose what to believe.</i>

604
00:33:49,569 --> 00:33:50,445
PROTECT LIFE

605
00:33:50,528 --> 00:33:53,948
[Marcus] <i>Because if we let them</i>
<i>write our story…</i>

606
00:33:54,032 --> 00:33:58,077
[Jalil] <i>We are also letting them</i>
<i>write our future.</i>

607
00:33:58,703 --> 00:34:01,581
There have been
many moments in our history

608
00:34:01,664 --> 00:34:04,125
when we believed that change was possible.

609
00:34:05,001 --> 00:34:09,130
Yet, history has repeatedly reminded us

610
00:34:09,881 --> 00:34:11,632
that a single victory

611
00:34:12,800 --> 00:34:14,510
is never enough if, afterwards,

612
00:34:14,594 --> 00:34:17,805
we forget, become complacent,

613
00:34:17,889 --> 00:34:20,266
and cease to be vigilant.

614
00:34:20,933 --> 00:34:23,603
[Natalia] <i>Because those who wish</i>
<i>to exploit our country</i>

615
00:34:23,686 --> 00:34:27,774
<i>know how to wait, how to hide,</i>

616
00:34:27,857 --> 00:34:29,734
<i>and know how to wear a different face.</i>

617
00:34:29,817 --> 00:34:32,695
<i>They also know how to make up stories</i>

618
00:34:33,362 --> 00:34:36,908
<i>that provoke us to turn</i>
<i>against one another</i>

619
00:34:36,991 --> 00:34:38,910
<i>instead of uniting.</i>

620
00:34:38,993 --> 00:34:41,496
Just as they did with Isla Damai.

621
00:34:41,579 --> 00:34:44,165
[Natalia] <i>With Datu Rahman.</i>
<i>With Jalil Abubakar.</i>

622
00:34:45,416 --> 00:34:48,211
<i>To a community that was easily</i>
<i>branded an enemy</i>

623
00:34:48,294 --> 00:34:49,837
<i>in the eyes of the nation,</i>

624
00:34:50,379 --> 00:34:53,216
<i>fueled by the fear and prejudice</i>

625
00:34:53,883 --> 00:34:57,220
<i>that has long been unfairly</i>
<i>attached to being Muslim.</i>

626
00:34:57,804 --> 00:35:01,099
If there is one thing
we can learn from all of this,

627
00:35:01,182 --> 00:35:05,186
it is that we should not use
our differences

628
00:35:05,269 --> 00:35:07,230
as an excuse to judge one another.

629
00:35:07,313 --> 00:35:10,316
For regardless of our faith,

630
00:35:10,399 --> 00:35:12,401
our aspirations are the same.

631
00:35:13,152 --> 00:35:16,155
Peace, justice,

632
00:35:16,864 --> 00:35:21,994
and a safe future for our loved ones.

633
00:35:22,495 --> 00:35:26,457
[Natalia] <i>And perhaps this is</i>
<i>where true unity begins.</i>

634
00:35:26,541 --> 00:35:29,627
<i>When we learn to look</i>

635
00:35:29,710 --> 00:35:31,879
<i>beyond our own fears,</i>

636
00:35:31,963 --> 00:35:33,881
<i>beyond our own sides,</i>

637
00:35:33,965 --> 00:35:37,343
<i>and beyond our own blood.</i>

638
00:35:38,302 --> 00:35:39,637
<i>The fight is not over yet.</i>

639
00:35:40,680 --> 00:35:44,308
And perhaps it never will be.

640
00:35:44,392 --> 00:35:46,602
[Natalia] <i>But as long</i>
<i>as there are Filipinos</i>

641
00:35:46,686 --> 00:35:49,480
<i>ready to stand up for the truth,</i>

642
00:35:49,564 --> 00:35:53,901
<i>to prioritize the welfare</i>
<i>of the many over self-interest,</i>

643
00:35:54,902 --> 00:35:59,949
<i>and to choose unity despite</i>
<i>our differences,</i>

644
00:36:01,075 --> 00:36:04,662
<i>the hope of our nation will remain alive.</i>

645
00:36:05,663 --> 00:36:08,082
Long live the Filipino people.

646
00:36:08,791 --> 00:36:11,085
Long live the Republic of the Philippines.

647
00:36:11,169 --> 00:36:13,671
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

648
00:36:13,754 --> 00:36:16,424
♪ <i>I will not remain silent anymore</i>
<i>This has to stop</i> ♪

649
00:36:16,507 --> 00:36:18,926
♪ <i>I refuse to be used anymore</i>
<i>Enough is enough</i> ♪

650
00:36:19,010 --> 00:36:21,888
♪ <i>I won't back down</i>
<i>I will fight</i> ♪

651
00:36:21,971 --> 00:36:25,183
♪ <i>Stand up and take a stand</i> ♪

652
00:36:26,976 --> 00:36:29,896
[tense stinging]

653
00:36:32,190 --> 00:36:36,819
["Maninindigan" by Marko Rudio playing]

654
00:36:46,829 --> 00:36:48,164
♪ <i>Today</i> ♪

655
00:36:49,165 --> 00:36:53,836
♪ <i>The morning is dark</i>
<i>Opening my eyes after a blink</i> ♪

656
00:36:53,920 --> 00:36:56,547
♪ <i>In the midst of terror</i> ♪

657
00:36:56,631 --> 00:36:57,924
[indistinct dialogue]

658
00:36:58,007 --> 00:37:00,051
- [quirky sting]
- [laughter]

659
